Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kimma L Mosay in court with attorney Kari S. Hoel.  Defendant Kimma L Mosay in custody.  Russell E. Berg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant shall be fingerprinted at the Barron County Sheriff's Dept., if not already done.
If represented by the Public Defender and does not have a phone, must contact the Public Defender weekly at 715-537-1191.

Defendant Kimma L Mosay in court with attorney Kari S. Hoel for today.  Defendant Kimma L Mosay in custody.  Angela Lynn Beranek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Eligible for Public Defender.  Defendant contests extradition.  Bond set.  Extradition hearing scheduled for December 17, 2014 at 09:00 am.
